<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFBDEF7EFF42F898FDF8F843" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFBDEF7EFF42F898FC0EF86F" blockId="21.[151,1436,1764,2044]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBDEF7EFF42F898FEE7F8FF" bold="true" box="[199,338,1837,1863]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Comments:</emphasis>
This species is currently considered as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFBDEF7EFB82F89BFB3EF8FF" box="[1031,1163,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopa">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBDEF7EFB82F89BFB3EF8FF" box="[1031,1163,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. chrysopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we follow here the proposition of Dr. H. Braun that suggested on the OSF database (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFBDEF7EFCF5F8E4FBE7F8D3" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[880,1106,1873,1899]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref30789" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. speciesfile. org (accessed 13 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBDEF7EFC5CF8E7FBA4F8D3" box="[985,1041,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
) that 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFBDEF7EFB14F8E7FB45F8D3" baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[1169,1264,1874,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBDEF7EFB14F8E7FB45F8D3" box="[1169,1264,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered as a valid species. The subgenital plates of males figured here, although similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFBDEF7EFB26F8C3FA92F837" box="[1187,1319,1909,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopa">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBDEF7EFB26F8C3FA92F837" box="[1187,1319,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. chrysopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, present a much more restricted terminal dilation, resembling a golf club head. The 
<typeStatus id="827FB2C9FFBDEF7EFC3AF82FFB94F80C" box="[959,1057,1946,1972]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFBDEF7EFBC1F82FFB70F80B" box="[1092,1221,1945,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysopa">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBDEF7EFBC1F82FFB70F80B" box="[1092,1221,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. chrysopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, otherwise, present terminal dilations that are much longer and wider, resembling a spatula.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFBDEF7EFF42F854FDF8F843" blockId="21.[151,1436,1764,2044]" box="[199,589,2017,2044]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFBDEF7EFF42F854FEEEF843" bold="true" box="[199,347,2017,2043]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
: Sound not recorded.
</paragraph>
